1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,930
This is a fact of paramount significance.

2
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:09,569
Each human being, whether he lives in India or Indianapolis, whether he's ignorant or brilliant,

3
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:14,209
civilized or uncivilized, young or old, has this desire.

4
00:00:14,479 --> 00:00:16,450
He wants to feel important.

5
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:18,049
Ponder on that.

6
00:00:18,319 --> 00:00:26,610
Everyone, yes everyone, your neighbor, you, your wife, your boss, has a natural desire to feel he is somebody.

7
00:00:26,959 --> 00:00:33,569
The desire to be important is man's strongest, most compelling non-biological hunger.

8
00:00:34,239 --> 00:00:40,209
Successful advertisers know that people crave prestige, distinction, recognition.

9
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:43,489
Headlines that produce sales read like this.

10
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:51,009
For smart young homemakers, persons with distinctive tastes use, you want only the best.

11
00:00:51,279 --> 00:00:53,249
Be the envy of everyone.

12
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:57,890
for women who want to be envied by women and admired by men.

13
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:04,850
These headlines, in effect, tell people, buy this product and you put yourself in the important class.

14
00:01:05,759 --> 00:01:11,729
Satisfying the craving, the hunger, to be important, carries you forward to success.

15
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:15,809
It is basic equipment in your success tool chest.

16
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:23,410
Yet, even though displaying the attitude, you are important, gets results, and even though it costs nothing,

17
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,009
few persons use it.

18
00:01:25,279 --> 00:01:28,288
A little fill-in is needed here to show why.

19
00:01:29,039 --> 00:01:38,528
On the philosophical side, our religions, our laws, our entire culture are based on the belief of the importance of the individual.

20
00:01:38,959 --> 00:01:45,890
Suppose, for example, you were flying your own plane and were forced down in an isolated mountain region.

21
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:50,930
As soon as your accident was known, a large-scale search for you would begin.

22
00:01:51,279 --> 00:01:54,209
No one would ask, is that fellow important?

23
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:59,809
Without knowing anything about you except that you are a human being, helicopters,

24
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:04,450
other aircraft, and searching parties on foot would begin looking for you.

25
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:09,569
and they would keep on looking for you, spending thousands of dollars in the process,

26
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:13,969
until they found you, or until not one trace of hope remained.

27
00:02:14,799 --> 00:02:19,330
When a little child wanders off into a woods, falls into a well,

28
00:02:19,330 --> 00:02:27,489
or gets into some other dangerous predicament, no one is concerned with whether or not the child comes from an important family.

29
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:33,009
Every effort is made to rescue the child, because every child is important.

30
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:41,410
It's not too wild to guess that of all living creatures, probably not more than one in ten million is a human being.

31
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:44,450
A person is a biological rarity.

32
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:48,049
He is important in God's scheme of things.

33
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,370
Now let's look at the practical side.

34
00:02:52,559 --> 00:03:00,209
When most people shift their thinking from philosophical discussions to everyday situations, they tend to forget,

35
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:05,809
unfortunately, their ivory tower concepts of the importance of individuals.

36
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:11,569
Tomorrow, take a good look at how most people exhibit an attitude that seems to say,

